of Age of Miracles, recently tweeted that we=E2=80=99ll get to net zero bef=
ore the most optimistic expectations, despite the fact that =E2=80=9Calmost=
 noone knows how or why we=E2=80=99ll achieve this.=E2=80=9D He=E2=80=99s b=
etting you can use solar to pull CO2 from the air and turn it into syntheti=
c fuels.=C2=A0
The grand challenge of, and incentives to prevent, the climate crisis have =
pulled in some of the smartest people in the world to use all the tools at =
humanity=E2=80=99s disposal to avoid disaster, and in the process, beat the=
 boss and advance to the next level of ENERGY: The Game.=C2=A0
Have Kids
Look, I tried to simplify millions of years of history and some very comple=
x, multi-causal events into one, clean narrative. I=E2=80=99m missing impor=
tant details, even getting some wrong.=C2=A0
But from this zoomed out view, the period that we=E2=80=99re living through=
 isn=E2=80=99t a tragedy, it=E2=80=99s a trial, and it will be a triumph.=
=C2=A0
Without the climate crisis, we would likely have ridden fossil fuels until =
it was too late. At that point, we wouldn=E2=80=99t have been able to power=
 a growing population or increasingly powerful machines. We might not have =
had the resources to develop, produce, and scale the next generation of ene=
rgy sources at all. Without the climate crisis, the future might have been =
bleak. That zero-sum, negative growth world would have been a bad one to br=
ing kids into.=C2=A0
Because of it, the world has accelerated the development and deployment of =
technologies like solar, fission, and fusion. We=E2=80=99re not out of the =
woods, but we have the tools to get out.=C2=A0
The moment we begin to reverse the effects of climate change, we=E2=80=99ll=
 have broken through to the next level, one in which we can manufacture ene=
rgy and consume as much of it as we would like without fear of killing the =
planet. That is enormous and unprecedented.=C2=A0
There will certainly be new problems and challenges. Utopia isn=E2=80=99t r=
eal, and we wouldn=E2=80=99t want it to be.=C2=A0
But if history is a guide, the next level in ENERGY will transform and impr=
ove society in ways that are impossible to predict from our current vantage=
 point, just as it would have been impossible to sketch the Industrial Revo=
lution by looking at the Newcomen Steam Engine.=C2=A0
If we get this right, our kids will live in a world that=E2=80=99s more abu=
ndant and more ethical than the one we inhabit today. They=E2=80=99ll look =
back at 2023 the same way we look back at 1712: wouldn=E2=80=99t want to li=
ve there, but thankful for the contributions of the people who did.=C2=A0
Climate change is real. It=E2=80=99s our current Boss. Defeating it will re=
quire deft gameplay from millions of people, governments, and businesses.=
=C2=A0
But it doesn=E2=80=99t spell inevitable doom, either. Humans are incredibly=
 adaptable, and against all odds, we=E2=80=99ve created exactly the right t=
ools to defeat it and unlock the next level at exactly the right time.=C2=
=A0
Having kids isn=E2=80=99t the problem; it=E2=80=99s the solution. It=E2=80=
=99s exactly because people who lived in much worse conditions than we do d=
ecided to have kids that we have the ultimate weapon in this game: human cr=
eativity.=C2=A0
Whatever challenges await on the next level, we=E2=80=99ll need all the kid=
s we can get to solve them.=C2=A0
So don=E2=80=99t listen to the doom and gloom. It=E2=80=99s counterproducti=
ve, depressing, and evil. It prioritizes clicks over your happiness and use=
s fear to sell ads [ https://substack.com/redirect/83450b59-295f-44ef-8e5e-=
9e3d68af163b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8Exk=
RNpU ]. The people pretending to be ethical by being pessimistic are not th=
e good guys; they=E2=80=99re villains in this game.=20
But villains can be useful, too. They=E2=80=99re part of the game. If that =
fear has motivated some of our best people to join the fight to beat the bo=
ss and unlock the next level, humanity is better off for it.=20
Just don=E2=80=99t let it depress you into hopeless inaction, right when th=
ings are about to get really good. Don=E2=80=99t let it stop you from bring=
ing kids into this world.=20
If we=E2=80=99re lucky, we might be alive to experience some of the wonders=
 of this next level. I certainly hope to be.=C2=A0
But I=E2=80=99m almost certain that our kids will be, and I am so excited f=
or them. What a time to be alive!

