16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But we don&#8217;t just need =
these new energy sources to fight climate change. We need them for three re=
asons:&#160;</p><ol style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margi=
n: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64=
); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding=
-left: 4px;">Fossil fuels will run out.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-le=
ft: 4px;">To unlock the next level of civilizational progress, we&#8217;ll =
need denser and more abundant energy sources.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"ma=
rgin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64,=
 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padd=
ing-left: 4px;">To solve climate change.&#160;</p></li></ol><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;"><strong>In other words, we would have needed to undertake this energy tr=
ansition with or without climate change. The threat of climate change may b=
e the only way that we can make it in time.&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;">Here&#8217;s what I mean.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217;re going=
 to need a lot more energy - and much denser energy &#8211; to unlock the n=
ext level of the game than fossil fuels can provide.&#160;</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px=
 0;"><span>Peak oil and gas estimates are always wrong &#8211; when the inc=
entives are aligned, we come up with new ways to discover new resources &#8=
211; but fossil fuels are not infinite. That&#8217;s the main challenge: </=
span><strong>fossil fuel supplies are finite, and demand for energy is not.=
</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In fact, not long a=
go, the main concern around fossil fuels was not that they would destroy th=
e planet, but that they would run out! In college, I took an Energy &amp; E=
conomics class, and the big theme was that we were going to run out of that=
