/span></p><blockquote style=3D"border-left: 4px solid #51b4e9; margin: 20px=
 0; padding: 0;"><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0; margin-left: 20px;"><em><span>But that&#8=
217;s where the bad news comes in. Our global civilization came at a huge c=
ost. We needed a whole bunch of energy to build it, and we got that energy =
by burning fossil fuels, which came from dead plants and animals buried dee=
p in the ground. </span><strong>We used up most of this fuel before you got=
 here, and now it&#8217;s pretty much all gone. This means that we no longe=
r have enough energy to keep our civilization running like it was before.</=
strong><span> So we&#8217;ve had to cut back. Big-time. We call this the </=
span><strong>Global Energy Crisis</strong><span>, and it&#8217;s been going=
