 style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">committing t=
o triple nuclear energy capacity by 2050, &#8220;recognizing the key role o=
f nuclear energy in reaching net zero.</a><span>&#8221;</span></p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;"><strong>Without the climate crisis, &#8220;environmentalists&#822=
1; may have succeeded in killing nuclear energy.</strong><span>&#160;</span=
></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>And then there&#8217;s fusion, the energy sour=
ce furthest along the tech tree. </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/red=
irect/fae19d9b-219b-4470-adac-acdf8ccc77a3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7Gn=
A_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); te=
xt-decoration: underline;">Fusion</a><span> has been a promising research p=
roject for nearly 80 years with no commercial success to show for it. At th=
e turn of the millennium, most of the world&#8217;s research efforts and do=
llars were channeled into one promising but glacially slow project &#8211; =
ITER &#8211; with a projected timeline of 2035-2040.&#160;</span></p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;">What&#8217;s happened since, however, is for all intents and pu=
rposes miraculous. A number of other branches of the tech tree &#8211; magn=
ets, simulation software, and controllers, to name three &#8211; have all h=
